<!-- AI Integration Guidelines -->
<h2>AI Integration Guidelines</h2>
<p>To ensure consistency and quality in AI-assisted code modifications, please adhere to the following guidelines:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Avoid Placeholders:</strong> AI tools should return complete code without placeholders. Ensure all variables and functions are fully defined and functional.</li>
    <li><strong>Preserve Existing Functions:</strong> When fixing errors, do not remove or alter existing functions unless they are directly related to the issue being addressed. This helps maintain the integrity of the codebase.</li>
    <li><strong>Patch Application:</strong> Consider experimenting with applying patches instead of returning entire code blocks. This can help minimize errors and maintain code consistency. Use the `git apply` command to manually apply patches if necessary.</li>
</ul>

